cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SI. 

The paper proposes a graph-theoretic model for time-inconsistent behavior in decision-making, which is a problem in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The analysis of the model involves computational complexity (cs.CC) and algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also explores ways to design tasks to motivate agents, which falls under social and information networks (cs.SI).
